      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:2:3:9:6",
      "text": [
        " إِنَّ اللَّهَ عَزَّ وَ جَلَّ أَوْحَى إِلَى مُوسَى بْنِ عِمْرَانَ ( عليه السلام ) إِذَا وَقَفْتَ بَيْنَ يَدَيَّ فَقِفْ مَوْقِفَ الذَّلِيلِ الْفَقِيرِ وَ إِذَا قَرَأْتَ التَّوْرَاةَ فَأَسْمِعْنِيهَا بِصَوْتٍ حَزِينٍ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ali Bin Ma’bad, from Abdullah Bin Al Qasim, from Abdullah Bin Sinan, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Allah<sup>azwj</sup> Mighty and Majestic Revealed unto Musa<sup>as</sup> Bin Imran<sup>as</sup>: “Whenever you<sup>as</sup> stand in front of Me<sup>azwj</sup>, so stand the standing of the disgraced one, the poor; and whenever you<sup>as</sup> recite the Torah, so make it to be heard in a grief-laden voice’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "6. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from Ali ibn Ma’bad from ‘Abd Allah ibn al-Qasim from ‘Abd Allah ibn Sinan from abu ‘Abd Allah  (a.s.) who has said the following: “Allah, the Most Majestic, the Most Holy, sent revelation to Moses son of ‘Imran, peace be upon him, ‘Whenever you stand before me, do so like a humble and poor person, whenever you read the Torah, read it with sad voice.’” "
        ]
      }
    },
